1 (d) (1) An applicant qualifies under this section if the applicant:
2 (i) subject to paragraph (2) of this subsection, has at least 12 years
3 of work experience in engineering that is satisfactory to the Board and that indicates to the
4 Board that the applicant may be competent to practice engineering; and
5 (ii) 1. has passed the examination IN THE FUNDAMENTALS OF
6 ENGINEERING GIVEN BY THE BOARD UNDER THIS SUBTITLE; AND
7 2. AFTER PASSING THE EXAMINATION IN THE
8 FUNDAMENTALS OF ENGINEERING, HAS PASSED THE EXAMINATION in the principles
9 and practice of engineering given by the Board under this subtitle.
10 (2) If an applicant has completed 1 or more years of a college or university
11 curriculum in engineering that the Board approves, it may allow, for each of those years, a
12 1–year credit towards the experience requirement of paragraph (1)(i) of this subsection.
13 (3) If an applicant has completed 1 or more years of a college or university
14 curriculum in engineering that has not been approved by the Board, the Board may allow,
15 for each of those years, a credit of up to 6 months towards the experience requirement under
16 paragraph (1)(i) of this subsection.
17 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
18 October 1, 2025.

